fields.description: Højlund hit the ground running with a hat-trick against Finland on the opening night of qualifying and then added two more to his tally in the 3-2 defeat by Kazakhstan. Just one goal behind his tally is the familiar name of Cristiano Ronaldo, who struck twice in each of Portugal's convincing victories over Liechtenstein and Luxembourg and now has 122 international goals to his name. Perhaps more unexpectedly, Scott McTominay is also on four goals having found the net twice as Scotland saw off Cyprus 3-0 and Spain with a famous 2-0 triumph.

fields.title: Premier League: rating of the best players from Russia, Kanchelskis, Kharin, Arshavin, Smertin, Pavlyuchenko, Bilyaletdinov, Pogrebnyak, Zhirkov - Championship
fields.description: In the history of the Premier League, there were several legionnaires from Russia. Andrei Kanchelskis, Alexei Smertin, Roman Pavlyuchenko, Andrei Arshavin, Diniyar Bilyaletdinov, Yuri Zhirkov and Pavel Pogrebnyak played and distinguished themselves there. This "Magnificent Seven", as well as goalkeeper Dmitry Kharin, are all Russians in the history of the Premier League.

fields.title: The leader of Arsenal returned after a terrible injury. Jesus Recovery Insider
fields.description:
In December, once it became clear that Gabriel Jesus had injured his knee in Brazil's World Cup squad, Arsenal had only one plan: to put the striker on a flight to London as soon as possible. Jesus was away, in Qatar, and was in a state of great emotional stress.

Forced to miss the rest of the World Cup is a painful blow for any player in any country. But it was especially disappointing for Jesus after the unsuccessful World Cup in Russia in 2018: he started every match of the team in the tournament, but did not score once. The player was eager to prove himself on the world stage, so for him, Qatar was not only about the collective desire for glory, but also about a personal mission.
